        {
            "text": "News Reports are driven by the reporter, most often using their own voice. In this kind of story the reporter takes us on a journey through the issue, either talking on camera or with a voice over. In the best narrated stories the reporter does more than just explain the story. The reporter creates drama through how he or she organizes and narrates the material. Reports can be audio or video stories.", 
